headline: Omnicom: Q3 Earnings Snapshot
summary: The New York-based company said it had profit of $1.75 per share. Earnings, adjusted for costs related to mergers and acquisitions and non-recurring costs, came to $2.24 per share. The results beat Wall Street expectations.

headline: Omnicom Group’s (NYSE:OMC) Q3 Earnings Results: Revenue In Line With Expectations
summary: Global advertising giant Omnicom Group (NYSE:OMC) met Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q3 CY2025, with sales up 4% year on year to $4.04 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $2.24 per share was 3.1% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
